oviders endpoint  ￼\n\t•\tRegion handling:\n\t•\tStore user region code (ISO-3166-1)\n\t•\tAlways request watch providers for that region\n\n4) Backend endpoints (REST)\n\nAuth required unless noted.\n\t•\tGET /v1/search?q\u003d\u0026type\u003dmovie|tv|book\u0026region\u003dUS\n\t•\tReturns normalized search results + availability summary (if available)\n\t•\tGET /v1/titles/:type/:externalId?region\u003dUS\n\t•\tReturns title detail + availability by offer type + lastVerifiedAt\n\t•\tPOST /v1/mustwatch\n\t•\tbody: { type, externalId, status: “mustwatch”|“watched”, note? }\n\t•\tGET /v1/mustwatch?userId\u003dme|:userId\u0026type\u003d\u0026privacyAware\u003dtrue\n\t•\tPATCH /v1/mustwatch/:id\n\t•\tbody: { status?, note?, removed? }\n\t•\tPOST /v1/follow\n\t•\tbody: { userIdToFollow }\n\t•\tDELETE /v1/follow/:userId\n\t•\tGET /v1/activity\n\t•\tReturns recommendations to me + following activity (filtered by privacy)\n\t•\tPOST /v1/recommendations\n\t•\tbody: { toUserIds: [], type, externalId, message? }\n\t•\tPOST /v1/recommendations/:id/read\n\t•\tPOST /v1/report\n\t•\tbody: { reportedUserId, reason, notes? }\n\n5) Database schema (Postgres)\n\t•\tusers\n\t•\tid (pk), displayName, username, avatarUrl, region, createdAt\n\t•\tfollows\n\t•\tfollowerId, followeeId, createdAt, unique(followerId, followeeId)\n\t•\ttitles_cache\n\t•\tid (pk), type, externalSource (“tmdb”), externalId, json, updatedAt\n\t•\tavailability_cache\n\t•\tid (pk), type, externalId, region, json, lastFetchedAt, lastVerifiedAt, ttlSeconds\n\t•\tunique(type, externalId, region)\n\t•\tmustwatch\n\t•\tid (pk), userId, type, externalId, status, note, createdAt, updatedAt, removedAt\n\t•\trecommendations\n\t•\tid (pk), fromUserId, toUserId, type, externalId, message, createdAt, readAt\n\t•\tprivacy_settings\n\t•\tuserId (pk), listVisibility (public|followers|private), activityVisibility (public|followers|private)\n\t•\tblocks\n\t•\tblockerId, blockedId, createdAt, unique(blockerId, blockedId)\n\n6) Caching + freshness rules\n\t•\ttitles_cache TTL: 7 days\n\t•\tavailability_cache TTL: 12–24 hours (region-dependent)\n\t•\tOn title detail load:\n\t•\tServe cached availability if within TTL\n\t•\tIf stale: refresh in background, update UI when complete\n\t•\tStore lastFetchedAt and lastVerifiedAt separately:\n\t•\tlastFetchedAt \u003d time data pulled from provider API\n\t•\tlastVerifiedAt \u003d time your service validated the response quality\n\n7) “Verify information and double check sources are current and accurate” command (implement as a mandatory backend guard)\n\nCreate a backend module: verifyAvailability()\n\nVerification checklist (must run on every availability refresh before writing to availability_cache):\n\t•\tValidate API response:\n\t•\tHTTP status success\n\t•\tRequired fields present for region payload\n\t•\tProvider list is non-empty or explicitly “no offers”\n\t•\tNormalize offer types into exactly:\n\t•\tfree, subscription, rent, buy\n\t•\tCross-check timestamps:\n\t•\tRecord fetch time\n\t•\tReject writes if response is older than the cached version (out-of-order responses)\n\t•\tEnforce TTL:\n\t•\tIf cache age \u003e ttlSeconds, mark UI status as “refreshing” until new data verified\n\t•\tSource-of-truth allowlist:\n\t•\tOnly accept provider data from configured sources (TMDb watch providers, or Watchmode/Streaming Availability API if enabled)\n\t•\tLog verification:\n\t•\tSave verification result (pass/fail + reason) for observability\n\nData-source notes:\n\t•\tTMDb watch providers endpoints are documented and intended for this usage pattern.  ￼\n\t•\tDo not incorporate scraped JustWatch data due to terms restrictions.  ￼\n\n8) UI acceptance criteria (prototype)\n\t•\tSearch:\n\t•\tDebounced search (300–500ms)\n\t•\tResults show provider chips when available\n\t•\tTitle detail:\n\t•\tAvailability grouped by offer type\n\t•\t“Last updated” line uses availability_cache.lastVerifiedAt\n\t•\tMust Watch:\n\t•\tAdd/remove/mark watched\n\t•\tPrivacy 