      "text": "This is a comprehensive product specification for **MustWatch Social**. To get the best results from a high-reasoning model like Gemini 1.5 Pro or Ultra, you should provide this blueprint as a \"System Instruction\" or a foundational prompt.\n\nBelow is the structured output, refined into a **technical implementation guide**. It includes the core logic for the requested `verifyAvailability()` module and the architectural scaffolding.\n\n---\n\n# MustWatch Social: Developer Blueprint\n\n## 1. System Architecture\n*   **Frontend:** React Native (Expo) for cross-platform iOS/Android.\n*   **Backend:** Node.js + Express (TypeScript) on Vercel/Render.\n*   **Database:** Supabase (PostgreSQL + Auth + Storage).\n*   **Primary External APIs:** \n    *   **Movies/TV:** TMDb (The Movie Database) API.\n    *   **Availability:** TMDb `/watch/providers` (Powered by JustWatch).\n    *   **Books:** Google Books API or OpenLibrary API.\n\n## 2. Database Schema (Prisma/SQL)\n```sql\n-- Core user profile\nCREATE TABLE profiles (\n  id UUID REFERENCES auth.users ON DELETE CASCADE PRIMARY KEY,\n  username TEXT UNIQUE,\n  display_name TEXT,\n  avatar_url TEXT,\n  region CHAR(2) DEFAULT \u0027US\u0027,\n  language CHAR(2) DEFAULT \u0027en\u0027,\n  list_visibility TEXT DEFAULT \u0027followers\u0027, -- public, followers, private\n  created_at TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE DEFAULT NOW()\n);\n\n-- Combined list for Movies, TV, and Books\nCREATE TABLE must_watch_items (\n  id BIGSERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\n  user_id UUID REFERENCES profiles(id),\n  external_id TEXT NOT NULL, -- TMDb ID or ISBN\n  media_type TEXT NOT NULL, -- \u0027movie\u0027, \u0027tv\u0027, \u0027book\u0027\n  status TEXT DEFAULT \u0027must_watch\u0027, -- \u0027must_watch\u0027, \u0027watched\u0027\n  note TEXT,\n  created_at TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE DEFAULT NOW(),\n  UNIQUE(user_id, external_id, media_type)\n);\n\n-- Availability Cache (Refreshed every 12-24h)\nCREATE TABLE availability_cache (\n  id BIGSERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\n  external_id TEXT NOT NULL,\n  media_type TEXT NOT NULL,\n  region CHAR(2) NOT NULL,\n  data JSONB,\n  last_verified_at TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE,\n  UNIQUE(external_id, media_type, region)\n);\n```\n\n## 3. The `verifyAvailability()` Logic\nThis backend module ensures data integrity and adherence to the \"No Scraping\" policy.\n\n```typescript\n// backend/src/services/availability.service.ts\n\ninterface ProviderResponse {\n  link: string;\n  flatrate?: any[];\n  rent?: any[];\n  buy?: any[];\n  free?: any[];\n}\n\nexport async function getVerifiedAvailability(id: string, type: \u0027movie\u0027 | \u0027tv\u0027, region: string) {\n  // 1. Check Cache\n  const cached \u003d await db.availability_cache.findFirst({\n    where: { external_id: id, media_type: type, region }\n  });\n\n  const TTL \u003d 12 * 60 * 60 * 1000; // 12 hours\n  if (cached \u0026\u0026 (Date.now() - cached.last_verified_at.getTime() \u003c TTL)) {\n    return cached.data;\n  }\n\n  // 2. Fetch from Official Source (TMDb)\n  try {\n    const response \u003d await axios.get(\n      `https://api.themoviedb.org/3/${type}/${id}/watch/providers`,\n      { params: { api_key: process.env.TMDB_KEY } }\n    );\n\n    const regionData: ProviderResponse \u003d response.data.results[region];\n\n    if (!regionData) return { status: \u0027no_offers\u0027, providers: [] };\n\n    // 3. Normalize Offer Taxonomy\n    const normalized \u003d {\n      subscription: regionData.flatrate || [],\n      rent: regionData.rent || [],\n      buy: regionData.buy || [],\n      free: regionData.free || [],\n      lastUpdated: new Date().toISOString()\n    };\n\n    // 4. Update Cache (Atomic Upsert)\n    await db.availability_cache.upsert({\n      where: { external_id_media_type_region: { external_id: id, media_type: type, region } },\n      update: { data: normalized, last_verified_at: new Date() },\n      create: { external_id: id, media_type: type, region, data: normalized, last_verified_at: new Date() }\n    });\n\n    return normalized;\n  } catch (error) {\n    console.error(\"Availability Verification Failed:\", error);\n    return cached ? cached.data : null; // Fallback to stale data if API fails\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## 4. Key UI Components (React Native)\n\n### Search Result Card\n```tsx\nconst ResultCard \u003d ({ item }) \u003d\u003e (\n  \u003cView style\u003d{styles.card}\u003e\n    \u003cImage source\u003d{{ uri: `https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w200${item.poster_path}` }} style\u003d{styles.poster} /\u003e\n    \u003cView style\u003d{styles.info}\u003e\n      \u003cText style\u003d{styles.title}\u003e{item.title || item.name}\u003c/Text\u003e\n      \u003cText style\u003d{styles.meta}\u003e{new Date(item.release_date).getFullYear()} • {item.media_type}\u003c/Text\u003e\n      \n      {/* Availability Mini-Row */}\n      \u003cView style\u003d{styles.providers}\u003e\n        {item.availability?.subscription?.slice(0, 3).map(p \u003d\u003e (\n          \u003cImage key\u003d{p.provider_id} source\u003d{{ uri: getProviderLogo(p.logo_path) }} style\u003d{styles.logo} /\u003e\n        ))}\n        {item.availability?.free?.length \u003e 0 \u0026\u0026 \u003cBadge text\u003d\"Free\" /\u003e}\n      \u003c/View\u003e\n    \u003c/View\u003e\n    \u003cTouchableOpacity onPress\u003d{() \u003d\u003e handleAdd(item.id)}\u003e\n      \u003cIcon name\u003d\"plus-circle\" size\u003d{32} /\u003e\n    \u003c/TouchableOpacity\u003e\n  \u003c/View\u003e\n);\n```\n\n## 5. Implementation Roadmap for Gemini\nTo have the AI generate the full code, use these sequential prompts:\n\n1.  **Phase 1 (Setup):** \"Generate a React Native (Expo) project structure with React Navigation (Bottom Tabs) following the Wireframe screens 1, 2, and 7.\"\n2.  **Phase 2 (API):** \"Write a Node.js Express service that integrates TMDb search and the Google Books API, normalizing the results into a single list format.\"\n3.  **Phase 3 (Availability):** \"Implement the `verifyAvailability` function provided in the blueprint, including a PostgreSQL schema for caching.\"\n4.  **Phase 4 (Social):** \"Create the \u0027Recommend\u0027 flow: a screen to select friends, an API endpoint to save the recommendation, and a function to trigger a push notification via Firebase.\"\n\n## 6. Compliance \u0026 Safety Checklist\n*   **Privacy:** All `GET /activity` and `GET /mustwatch` queries must include a `WHERE` clause checking if the `requesting_user` is in the `followers` list of the `target_user` (unless visibility is \u0027public\u0027).\n*   **JustWatch Terms:** Ensure the UI displays the \"Powered by JustWatch\" attribution logo near any streaming data, as required by the TMDb/JustWatch data agreement.\n*   **Rate Limiting:** Implement a 1-second debounce on the search bar to stay within TMDb API rate limits.",
